h3. Issue summary
Changing the colour for _Link Colour_ and _Menu Item Highlight Background Color_ in Look and Feel configuration isn't working.

h3. Steps to reproduce
 # Go to Administration > System > Look and Feel
 # Modify the colour for _Link Colour_ and _Menu Item Highlight Background Color_
 # Refresh the page and go to the system dashboard.

!1.png|thumbnail!

h3. Expected results
The selected colour should change the link colours everywhere in JIRA.
 
h3. Actual results
 # The link colours didn't change it Activity Stream gadget.
 # The Menu Item Highlight Background Color remained blue.

!2.png|thumbnail!

h3. Workaround
Apply this on the announcement banner changing the colours/colour codes to what you require :
{code}
</style>
<style type="text/css">
.aui-button.aui-button-primary {
color: #CC0000 !important;
background: #fff;
border-color: #ccc;
}

.aui-button.aui-button-primary:hover {
color: #CC0000 !important;
background: #fff !important;
border-color: #ccc !important;
}

#dashboard>.tabs.vertical a, #dashboard>.tabs.vertical li.active {
color: #CC0000 !important;
}

#dashboard>.tabs.vertical a:hover {
color: #7a0000 !important;
}

.aui-page-panel-nav .tabs.vertical strong {
color: #CC0000 !important;
}

.aui-navgroup-vertical .aui-nav .aui-nav-selected a {
color: #fc2d3f !important;
}

.aui-dropdown2.aui-style-default a:hover {
background-color: #9a9a9a !important;
}
</style>
{code}

