h3. Problem Definition

Sometimes when trying to navigate to a Project in JIRA, instead of clicking on a link one might try and type in the Project Key from memory, e.g.:
{code:java}
http://jira-base-url:8080/projects/projectkey

{code}
This however will fail even if there does exist a Project with key PROJECTKEY.

The correct URL that would have worked is instead
{code:java}
http://jira-base-url:8080/projects/PROJECTKEY

{code}
which would in turn redirect to something else depending on access and Project Type such as {{.../projects/PROJECTKEY/issues}}, or the Board for PROJECTKEY, etc.
h3. Suggested Solution

Automatically redirect based on proper capitalization of the key in the URL.

