EPIC 1

h3. Problem

There is an inconsistency in the rendering of Column View by rendering an Issue Status in an XML Export (not as a Status of the currently exported Issue, but as a part of a Customfield that refers to another Issue)

All fields, that extend *NavigableFieldImpl*, have to implement *getColumnViewHtml(@Nullable final SimpleStatus status, @Nonnull Map<String, Object> displayParams)* .
 In most of them, the VelocityContext is correctly built using *NavigableFieldImpl.getVelocityParams(...),* directly from the *getColumnViewHtml()* method, or indirectly through an Helper (like *ColumnViewDateTimeHelper* for Date fields).

But, in case of *StatusSystemField*, the class *com.atlassian.jira.issue.status.DefaultStatusFormatter* builds a wrong context.
Instead of adding the *displayParams* in the context, it merge it into.

It causes that in {{jira-core/src/main/resources/templates/jira/issue/field/status-columnview.vm}}, the evaluation of *#if "($displayParams.textOnly || $displayParams.print_view)* is always false, and the rendering is always done using the SOY Template (issue-status-plugin-1.1.7.jar\templates/status.soy), the with HTML Code.

h3. Workaround

Copy the displayParams into itself before callinf the getColumnViewHtml() method ...
{code:java}
if (_field instanceof StatusSystemField) {
	_displayParams.put("displayParams", ImmutableMap.copyOf(_displayParams));
}

{code}

